<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Praying together brings us into God's presence.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Being filled with the Holy Spirit isn't something that happens every time you have a prayer group. Receiving the Holy Spirit and being filled with it are not the same thing.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Being filled with the Holy Spirit can provide an extra and immense level of boldness and confidence in our faith to share the Gospel with others, become convicted of sins in our own lives, or have some greater level of peace during very tough times.</li></ul></body></html>